22 (1) The insurer does not have is not required to allow a covered person to attend
23 the first-level grievance review. A covered person may submit written
24 material. Except as provided in subdivision (3) of this subsection, within three
25 business days after receiving a grievance, the insurer shall provide the covered
26 person with the name, address, and telephone number of the coordinator and
27 information on where and how to submit written material.material for the
28 first-level grievance review, including contact information for the insurer.
29 (2) An insurer shall issue a written decision, in clear terms, to the covered person
30 and, if applicable, to the covered person's provider, within 30 days after
31 receiving a grievance. The person or persons reviewing the grievance shall not
32 be the same person or persons who initially handled the matter that is the
33 subject of the grievance and, if the issue is a clinical one, at least one of whom
34 shall be a medical doctor with appropriate expertise to evaluate the matter.
35 Except as provided in subdivision (3) of this subsection, if the decision is not
36 in favor of the covered person, the written decision issued in a first-level
37 grievance review shall contain:contain all of the following information:
38 a. The professional qualifications and licensure of the person or persons
39 reviewing the grievance.
40 b. A statement of the reviewers' understanding basis of the grievance.
41 c. The reviewers' insurer's decision in clear terms and the contractual
42 basis or medical rationale in sufficient detail for the covered person to
43 respond further to the insurer's position.
44 …."
