34 (j1) Requirements Applicable to Appeals Reviews. – All of the following requirements
35 apply to an appeals review:
36 (1) Except as otherwise provided, appeals shall be reviewed by a licensed
37 physician who meets all of the following criteria:
38 a. Possesses a current and valid non-restricted license to practice
39 medicine in any United States jurisdiction.
40 b. Has practiced for a period of at least three consecutive years in the
41 same or similar specialty as a medical doctor who typically manages
42 the medical condition or disease for which prior authorization review
43 is required or whose training and experience meets all of the following
44 criteria:
45 1. Includes treatment of the same condition as the condition of
46 the covered person.
47 2. Includes treatment of complications that may result from the
48 service or procedure that is the subject of the appeal.
49 3. Is sufficient for the medical doctor to determine if the service
50 or procedure is medically necessary or clinically appropriate.
