1 c. Had no direct involvement in making the prior adverse determination
2 or noncertification that is the subject of the appeal.
3 d. Has no financial interest, or other conflict of interest, in the outcome
4 of the appeal.
5 (2) Appeals initiated by a licensed mental health professional for a service
6 provided by a licensed mental health professional may be reviewed by a
7 licensed mental health professional rather than a medical doctor. The
